TN, Tax Returns, Education, and How They’re Related

Savage Squadron, February 3, 2018

Income Distribution Amongst TN Counties (2011-2015)

Plotting a histogram of the average income per tax returns for these years shows us that the majority of households fall between $8000 and $14000.

The lowest county being Madison County in 2011, and the highest with Williamson County in 2015.

According to the Census ACS 1-year survey, the median household income for Tennessee was $48,547 in 2016, the latest figures available. Compared to the median US household income, Tennessee median household income is $9,070 lower. 

Change in Income (2011-2015)

** The majority of counties maintain their rank amongst other counties. 

Counties With the Highest Number of Tax Filers Per Year

Nashville/Davidson County’s growth is no surprise. Both the cost of survival and downtown traffic can tell you this much. By the looks of these graphs (and now personal knowledge as a resident in 2018), we can assume the population growth is only going to increase.

Shelby County, on the other hand, is another story. This county has the highest decrease in tax filers between these years, yet maintains the highest amount of total income returns every year. 

Overall Education Pct Regarding Student 
Graduation, Dropout, and Suspension

Now we get into the education data. Plotting these graphs provide some insight with regards to the highest and lowest counties.

  • Graduation rate is highest in Meigs, lowest in Shelby.
  • Dropout rate is highest in Shelby county, while kids are studious in Pickett and Meigs counties.
  • Teachers seem to be very strict in Shelby county, since it holds the highest student suspension rate.
Overall Education Pct Regarding Student 
ACT Scores, Math, Science, and Literature
  • Williamson county is showing highest ACT scores, average mathematics, literature, and second highest in science scores.
  • The lowest ACT scores are from Lake and Fayette counties
  • The lowest mathematics scores are from Cheatham and Putnam counties.
  • Fentress takes the lead for the highest science scores at 100%, with Lake being lowest, and Shelby 3rd lowest.
  • The lowest literature scores are from Hancock county.

Ok.. So now we are starting to see a trend. Both Shelby and Williamson County have appeared multiple times in our research. Are there any commonalities? 

Average ACT Scores Per Core Region Within TN

Mid Cumberland show the highest average overall, which also includes Williamson county.

Can you guess who falls within the Southwest Memphis region?? I’ll give you a hint.

It starts with “Shel” and ends with “by”.. 

Income VS. Dropout, Graduation, ACT Scores

Low: <= 40.87K / Mid: > 40.87K / High: > 48.56K / Very High: > 60K

Now we get into the interesting stuff.

We notice that the medium and high income groups rank highest across all three variables. One thing that is consistent about all three is Williamson and Shelby. Shelby is an outlier in each case regarding Dropout and Graduation, whereas Williamson is the outlier in ACT scores, as well as Shelby.

So what does this tell us?? In general, higher income ranges do not have a huge affect on student education levels compared to the lower. In fact, student that live in counties with a med/high income tend to do better than students within a low or very high income bucket. 

Act Scores Black and Hispanic Populations

This graph really helps paint a better picture regarding ACT vs Income, while also incorporating racial demographics as a factor.

With color relating to race, and size shown by income levels, you can pretty clearly see that there is not a consistent trend regarding income. There are some counties with a high income level doing FANTASTIC on the ACT (such as Williamson at 23.8), as well as some mid level counties. Similarly, there are some higher incomes doing POORLY on the ACT.

However, there does seem to be at least a small, but not insignificant, correlation between the racial population and education levels within counties. As this graph portrays, counties with a higher black population tend to do worse on the ACT vs the hispanic population, with the highest being.. >Shelby at 78.4% black population.
